Iterator<String> iterator = map.keySet().iterator();
Enumeration<String> enumeration = Collections.enumeration(iterator);

Explanation: $EXPLANATION:
The Collections.enumeration() method is a utility method that converts an Iterator to an Enumeration. In this case, we are converting an Iterator over the keys of the HashMap to an Enumeration. This is a simple and efficient way to convert between the two.

Note: This method is deprecated since Java 9. In Java 9 and later, you should use the Iterator.next method directly.

